column4: E: Could not get lock /var/lib/dpkg/lock - open (11 Resource temporarily unavailable)
E: Unable to lock the administration directory (/var/lib/dpkg/), is another process using it?
when i try to install ia32-libs.. i get that error
check and be sure ubuntu isn't checking for updates.  look at the icons in the system tray.  if it's looking for updates the icon will be gray.  if it is, that's what's using dpkg.
